{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":320,"text":"The sky is inherently democratic."},{"time":3079,"text":"It's accessible, in principle, anyway,\nby anyone, everywhere,"},{"time":7366,"text":"just simply by the act of looking up."},{"time":10485,"text":"But like so many\nbeautiful things around us,"},{"time":13474,"text":"it's slipping away from us,\nand we haven't even noticed,"},{"time":16462,"text":"because we're honestly not really looking."},{"time":19647,"text":"So what do we look at instead?"},{"time":21668,"text":"Well, we look at our phones,\nwe look at our computers,"},{"time":25780,"text":"we look at screens of all kinds."},{"time":27477,"text":"And honestly, we rarely\neven take the trouble"},{"time":30330,"text":"to look up enough to see each other,"},{"time":32702,"text":"let alone taking that next step\nto looking up at the actual sky."},{"time":37625,"text":"Now, there's a tendency to think\nthat the loss of our dark night skies"},{"time":42663,"text":"is the inevitable outcome\nof progress, change, technology."},{"time":46637,"text":"And you know, that's just simply not true."},{"time":48734,"text":"Later on, I'll tell you why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50985,"text":"But first, I want to tell you\nabout my experience of the dark night sky."},{"time":55091,"text":"I never saw a truly dark night\nsky until I was 15."},{"time":59225,"text":"I was here, in Arizona."},{"time":61649,"text":"I was on a road trip;\nI pulled over somewhere."},{"time":64939,"text":"I have no idea where I was,\nexcept I know what state."},{"time":68339,"text":"And I looked up,"},{"time":69760,"text":"and the sky was just filled\nwith an impossible number of stars."},{"time":74833,"text":"You see, I'm from New York City,"},{"time":76976,"text":"and in New York, you can see the moon,\nyou can see a couple of stars."},{"time":82067,"text":"More often than not, they turn out\nto be airplanes when they land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85260,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86293,"text":"But there's really not much else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87923,"text":"As a result, most of my colleagues\nwho are astronomers"},{"time":91502,"text":"spent at least part of their youth\nlooking up at the sky in their backyard."},{"time":95595,"text":"I never really had that experience,"},{"time":97584,"text":"and, as a result, I'm really\ndisappointing on camping trips."},{"time":101404,"text":"I don't really know many constellations."},{"time":104311,"text":"The ones I do know,\nyou probably know them, too."},{"time":107926,"text":"But I'll never forget that experience"},{"time":110281,"text":"of the first time I saw\nthe dark night sky."},{"time":112934,"text":"And I was just flabbergasted\nat how many stars there were."},{"time":117036,"text":"And I felt tiny."},{"time":119923,"text":"Then I also felt like,\n\"Where's this been hiding this whole time?"},{"time":125279,"text":"Who's been hiding this sky from me?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":128030,"text":"Of course, the answer is obvious\nif you think about it"},{"time":131336,"text":"or if you look at the picture on the left,"},{"time":133459,"text":"where you're seeing the same neighborhood\ntaken during a blackout"},{"time":138205,"text":"versus on an ordinary night."},{"time":140253,"text":"You can't see the stars\nif you drown them out with light."},{"time":144497,"text":"Take a look at our planet."},{"time":146194,"text":"This is our planet from space."},{"time":148200,"text":"Unlike stars, which are hot and glow\ninvisible light so we can see them,"},{"time":153359,"text":"our planet is, astronomically\nspeaking, pretty cold."},{"time":157703,"text":"So it doesn't really glow."},{"time":159798,"text":"When you see the planet looking\nlike a blue-green marble"},{"time":163481,"text":"the way it does in this picture,"},{"time":165059,"text":"you're seeing it because the sunlight\nis reflecting off of it,"},{"time":168343,"text":"and that's why you can see\nthe oceans, the clouds, the land."},{"time":171950,"text":"So if the sun wasn't shining on it,"},{"time":173877,"text":"we wouldn't be able\nto see the earth, right?"},{"time":177016,"text":"Or would we?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179293,"text":"This is our earth at night,"},{"time":181292,"text":"and it is one of the most\nstriking examples"},{"time":183427,"text":"of how we have affected\nour planet on a global scale."},{"time":186713,"text":"You can see light spidering out\nacross the globe everywhere."},{"time":191304,"text":"Now, of course, there are broad expanses\nof ocean that are still dark,"},{"time":194732,"text":"and in many underdeveloped areas\nthere's still darkness."},{"time":198670,"text":"But you'll notice\nthat this is a pretty global effect."},{"time":204163,"text":"We tend to think, when we think\nof places being lit up,"},{"time":207223,"text":"of very extreme examples --\nTimes Square, the Vegas Strip."},{"time":211670,"text":"But really what that picture shows you"},{"time":213769,"text":"is that it's not just\nthese extreme examples,"},{"time":216323,"text":"it's anywhere that uses outdoor lighting."},{"time":219073,"text":"This tends to be a really\ndramatic effect on the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222663,"text":"To understand why,"},{"time":223914,"text":"all you really have to do\nis think about the shape of a lightbulb."},{"time":227160,"text":"The lightbulb, for all practical purposes,"},{"time":229487,"text":"is more or less round."},{"time":231589,"text":"This is great for its original intended\npurpose of lighting up the indoors."},{"time":235412,"text":"You turn it on, light goes everywhere."},{"time":237580,"text":"An individual light bulb can light up\nyour whole room, more or less."},{"time":241367,"text":"Now, that's great\nif you're lighting the indoors,"},{"time":244485,"text":"but in its application\nin outdoor lighting,"},{"time":247279,"text":"that traditional shape of the light bulb,"},{"time":249283,"text":"the sort of globe that spreads\nlight everywhere,"},{"time":252309,"text":"is actually very inefficient."},{"time":254037,"text":"When you're outdoors,\nmostly what you care about"},{"time":256443,"text":"is lighting the ground beneath you\nand your immediate surroundings."},{"time":260544,"text":"All of that light that gets scattered\noutwards and upwards"},{"time":264566,"text":"doesn't actually help you\nlight the area around you."},{"time":267020,"text":"What it does is scatters up into the sky"},{"time":269657,"text":"and becomes what we call\n\"light pollution.\""},{"time":271732,"text":"Even if you don't care anything\nabout stargazing, this should worry you,"},{"time":276413,"text":"because it means that 60-70% of the energy\nwe use to light the outdoors"},{"time":281296,"text":"is wasted by blotting out the stars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285625,"text":"Now, like I said,\nI'm a big fan of technology."},{"time":288473,"text":"Obviously, I use technology\nevery day; I'm a scientist."},{"time":292208,"text":"And there's this tendency\nto say that it's progress that --"},{"time":295441,"text":"you know, I'm not suggesting\nwe're going to all go live by candlelight."},{"time":300565,"text":"Indeed, technology is allowing us\nto access the sky"},{"time":304398,"text":"in ways that are impossible otherwise."},{"time":306874,"text":"One of the greatest examples of this is,\nof course, the Hubble Space Telescope."},{"time":311203,"text":"The Hubble went up into space,\nit returns pictures daily,"},{"time":315184,"text":"and it allows us to see things"},{"time":316759,"text":"that we are incapable of seeing\nwith our naked eye,"},{"time":320000,"text":"in ways that we've never been able\nto do before in all of human history."},{"time":324971,"text":"Other examples of this\nwould be planetarium shows."},{"time":328052,"text":"In the past couple of years, planetarium\nshows have become more high-tech"},{"time":332248,"text":"with these great visualizations,"},{"time":334208,"text":"and even though this isn't access\ndirectly to the sky,"},{"time":336756,"text":"it's at least access\nto our knowledge about the sky."},{"time":339695,"text":"And indeed, we can experience\nthe sky in a planetarium"},{"time":342471,"text":"in a way that is impossible for us to do"},{"time":345184,"text":"just sitting out and looking in the dark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348441,"text":"All of you have heard of the Hubble\nSpace Telescope and of planetariums."},{"time":352285,"text":"But there are also ways\nfor technology to enable participation"},{"time":356278,"text":"in people's experience of the sky"},{"time":358177,"text":"that you may not be familiar with."},{"time":359895,"text":"These are called\n\"citizen science projects.\""},{"time":362556,"text":"Citizen science is when large\nresearch projects put their data online,"},{"time":367120,"text":"teach ordinary people, like you,\nto go and interact with that data"},{"time":371740,"text":"and actually contribute to the research"},{"time":373771,"text":"by making interesting or necessary\ncharacterizations about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377942,"text":"One such example of this is what\nI'm showing here, called \"Galaxy Zoo.\""},{"time":382237,"text":"Galaxy Zoo is a project"},{"time":384421,"text":"where people get a 20-minute --\neven less than that, actually -- tutorial"},{"time":389748,"text":"on how to interact\nwith these images of galaxies."},{"time":392864,"text":"They learn to annotate the images,"},{"time":394946,"text":"and within a couple of minutes,\nthey're up and running,"},{"time":397582,"text":"and they're making really\nuseful categorizations"},{"time":399888,"text":"and classifications of these galaxies."},{"time":401912,"text":"Now, it's easy to understand"},{"time":403445,"text":"why Galaxy Zoo would be an easy sell\nfor people to be involved with:"},{"time":407658,"text":"it involves pretty pictures;"},{"time":409072,"text":"galaxies are, generally\nspeaking, pretty attractive."},{"time":412073,"text":"However, there are many other flavors\nof citizen science projects"},{"time":415412,"text":"that people have delved into"},{"time":417088,"text":"that have varying levels of abstraction,"},{"time":420480,"text":"that you wouldn't necessarily think\npeople would jump at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423250,"text":"One such example of this\nis the citizen science project"},{"time":427183,"text":"associated with the mission\nthat I'm part of,"},{"time":430403,"text":"called the Kepler Mission."},{"time":431803,"text":"Kepler is a space telescope and it looks\nfor planets around other stars"},{"time":436487,"text":"by measuring the light\nfrom those stars very precisely."},{"time":439605,"text":"And we're looking for the dimmings"},{"time":441868,"text":"caused by stars blocking off\nsome of that light."},{"time":445785,"text":"We have an associated citizen science\nproject called \"Planet Hunters.\""},{"time":450023,"text":"Planet Hunters gives you,\nlike Galaxy Zoo, a short tutorial,"},{"time":454598,"text":"and within a couple of minutes,\nyou're up and running;"},{"time":457187,"text":"you're looking at data\nfrom the Kepler Mission"},{"time":459516,"text":"and looking for planets."},{"time":462030,"text":"The idea behind this\nis an easy sell, right?"},{"time":464865,"text":"But the actual process of planet-hunting\ninvolves a lot of looking at graphs,"},{"time":469758,"text":"like the one I'm showing you here,\nand annotating them."},{"time":472673,"text":"I do this all day and that doesn't even\nsound that interesting to me."},{"time":476915,"text":"However, not only are people\ninterested in doing this,"},{"time":480850,"text":"but the citizen scientists\nthat work with Planet Hunters"},{"time":484117,"text":"have actually found planets in the data"},{"time":487033,"text":"that would have gone\nundiscovered otherwise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489390,"text":"This is an author list\nfrom the paper that they published"},{"time":492402,"text":"of the planet they discovered."},{"time":493998,"text":"You'll see that all the people\nwho contributed are listed below,"},{"time":497096,"text":"and it's sort of an odd amalgam\nof people's real names"},{"time":500285,"text":"and their log-in names."},{"time":502053,"text":"You'll notice if you look carefully,\nthis is the first academic acknowledgment"},{"time":505823,"text":"of the importance of Irish coffee\nin the discovery process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509076,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510812,"text":"I don't want to give you the idea\nthat these are some out-of-work scientists"},{"time":515134,"text":"or just a bunch of nerds\nthat are really into this."},{"time":517894,"text":"There are 60,000 people\nwho participate in these projects,"},{"time":521142,"text":"and most of them don't have\ntechnical backgrounds."},{"time":523755,"text":"So clearly, what this is feeding into\nis people's curiosity"},{"time":527508,"text":"and their willingness to be part\nof the scientific discovery process."},{"time":531308,"text":"People want to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533929,"text":"But all of this technology"},{"time":536386,"text":"and all these digitally mediated ways\nof experiencing the sky"},{"time":540218,"text":"still have something of a feel to me\nlike looking at an animal in a zoo."},{"time":545151,"text":"It's a valid way\nof experiencing that thing --"},{"time":547796,"text":"indeed, the lion in the cage\nis still real,"},{"time":550601,"text":"the Hubble images are indeed real,"},{"time":552761,"text":"and you can get closer to a lion in a zoo\nthan you can in the wild."},{"time":557727,"text":"However, it's missing something."},{"time":560447,"text":"It's missing that savage beauty"},{"time":562613,"text":"of experiencing that very thing\nin the wild for yourself,"},{"time":566174,"text":"unmediated by a screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569042,"text":"The experience of looking up"},{"time":571301,"text":"and knowing that the sky you're looking at\nsurrounds every known living thing"},{"time":576744,"text":"in the universe"},{"time":578058,"text":"is very profound."},{"time":579798,"text":"Think about that for a moment."},{"time":581294,"text":"We are the only planet we know of\nthat has life on it."},{"time":586392,"text":"The sky that you see is shared\nby every other living thing"},{"time":589654,"text":"that we know of in existence."},{"time":592654,"text":"One of the things\nthat I really like about my work"},{"time":595655,"text":"is that it allows me to step back\nfrom my every day"},{"time":599084,"text":"and to experience the larger context,"},{"time":602824,"text":"this feeling that just as we go out\nand try to find planets in the universe"},{"time":608567,"text":"that might be like ours,"},{"time":610424,"text":"it always reminds me\nof how precious what we have here is."},{"time":615752,"text":"Our night sky is like a natural resource,"},{"time":618796,"text":"it's as though it's a park\nthat you can visit"},{"time":621603,"text":"without ever having to travel there."},{"time":624150,"text":"But like any natural resource,"},{"time":626155,"text":"if we don't protect it,\nif we don't preserve it and treasure it,"},{"time":629462,"text":"it will slip away from us and be gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632407,"text":"So if you're interested in this,"},{"time":634728,"text":"and this is something\nyou want to learn more about,"},{"time":637438,"text":"I encourage you in particular\nto visit darksky.org"},{"time":640814,"text":"and to learn more\nabout the choices you can make"},{"time":643195,"text":"that can protect the dark night sky,"},{"time":645485,"text":"because it belongs to everyone,\nit belongs to all of us,"},{"time":648742,"text":"and therefore, it's ours\nto experience as we wish."},{"time":651681,"text":"And it's also ours to lose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653345,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654620,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}